John Ntouskos, aka Dousk, is a new artist from Greece. Born in Athens in 1979, he completed his classical music studies in 1999. He is currently studying economics at the University of Patras in Greece, though most of his time is spent in front of a computer in his home studio. dousk has also produced music for radio and TV ads during the past two years. Zar, also known as The Shanbehzadeh Ensemble (Persian: گروه شنبه زاده) is an Iranian folk-jazz band, formed in Bushehr, Iran in 1990. The band offers a rare perspective on the traditional music and dance of the Persian Gulf, more specifically that of the southern Iranian coast. The principal instruments of the ensemble are the neyanbān (bagpipe), ney-jofti (flute), dammām (drum), zarbetempo (percussion), traditional flute, senj (cymbal) and boogh (a goat's horn). The Offline is an instrumental cinematic soul project based in Hamburg, Germany. Inspired by moody soundtracks of 1960s and 1970s film composers (Francois de Roubaix, Brian Bennet, David Axelrod et al.), The Offline releases atmospheric, soulfully visual tunes with dramatic library-music-esque cinematic arrangements. The Offline came to life, when composer and photographer Felix Müller travelled the Atlantic coastline in the south of France with his analogue camera, capturing beach life on film.
